values:
Dear journal,
I forgot you for a few years now. its amazing how tonight of all nights I feel the urge to write again - I'm also amazed that my friends still write in their journals. I'm still not a writer, but I've regressed and become so much more of a .. I don't even know. Seems like these days i feel less human then I was in college. Seems like I spent the better portion of 2009 digging at the past... and something that would never become anything more then it was. I was holding on. The goal of 2010 is to move forward... and find myself again. To find what's real... and stop being a robot... I need to remember what its like to feel, and be real. 
too deep - so I'm sitting in laura's apartment - she pays $550 a month for what has become the best deal i've seen. She has no bugs, its clean, and her heater hasn't exploded - its amazing how my standards have gone down. I love my house - even with the problems i've had... but i'm ready to move on. Everything reminds me of a time in my life that is over. I'm ready for a clean start, something new and exciting. Someone new. Maybe that's why i'm inspired to write tonight. Let the snow wash me clean of my past, and give me the strength to move on to a new future. 
The snow, which is really giving us another 18 inches on top of the 20 or so we got the other day has given me a lighter work load and quality time with my girls. Its falling steadily even at 1am, and the sky looks like daylight as the flakes and coat sticking to the ground reflect the ambient night light back into the sky. its beautiful. I feel whole again. i've forgiven him... not directly, but in my heart. of sorts... i say that with the twinge that i'm not quite there yet - but i hope i will be soon. This time, there is no going back. for the first time in my life, there will be no more chances for anyone who has has a chance, again. Thank you lord, for the group of friends I've found here at PCOM. they've befriended me despite the pain and anger and insecurities i've been fighting with since August. Granted, they're not the usual crowd i dwell with, but i think its time for me to step up my game, for myself. I am not the tiniest, the prettiest, the most sought after, or the smartest in our group. I don't get the most guys, i'm not the most guy crazy, and i'm neither the most immature or the most mature. Thus,allowing every insecurity i've ever had to surface. Since i'm taking time to get over all my past relationships, i may as well get over all my internal conflicts. i can't wait to see who i am when i'm done. i really started out from beyond broken this summer... and i already feel so much stronger, independent and whole. I've learned to cherish my career and my friendships and i'm working on myself, and making connections, and nurturing those connections. Especially the connections of close friends, new friends, and family. I could not have done any of this without my family. I've become so much closer to my brother and my dad then I have ever been over the past months. I love it! Of course i've started listening to jewel again... when do i ever go through a mental growing phase that jewel hasn't been present for? Spirit, every day. I run 2 miles every other day now, and I study like its my job. I'm still depressed on a daily basis, and my demons torture me daily, even in my dreams... but i'll win in the end. 
So, snow... wash me clean, and let me make myself whole... let 2010 bring good change to my life. <3

therea re two types of transitions... first, and the better type is the kind you are so ready for. you've not enjoyed the situation you've been in, but you made the best of it, you pushed through and now you are beyond ready for change. you accept change with passion and you enjy the new chapters that life brings you to, you actualy rarely compare the past to the present, and you are just enjoying the new change or the transition changes to the new change. 
then there's the type that compares ot the endof college. you came from transition number 1 into a great time. i loved my room, i loved my positions (president, senior, high and mighty in all ways... well of sorts, some of that may be a product of senioritis) having been there, done that whenever someone needs advice... ready to party and you have al of your friends by your side becasue you are on top... the year gues by and you have a great time, so many memories...  some good and amazing, some not so good but you get over that because this you know is the time of your life. then ti ends... you knew it was comming.. but it ended and now what do you do? nothing you do from now on can compare to the best time of your life.... where do you go from here? i have to wonder, what in life can top the best time of your life, and what do you do after its over? 

that's quite the question - another one is "who am i, and what do i want to do with my life?" how can i make an impact on the world? 
any help would be great... for now its tequila night on emeril live.

October: (googoo dolls: let love in)
- my residents were great - steph is fun, ash is nice - but when it came to decorating they al forgot we had a time arranged, so i had to run through the house yelling, and i was very sad with them. then they decorated and some (katie ringler) complained about me.
- on the 6th brett and i got in a fight because i was dancing wtih some guy at a party. jesse was DJing, and we stopped talking - later that night steve told me that j wanted to date me, and i was shocked. we all went to the diner, and though j sympathized, he didnt talk to me about anything in particular - confused, a week later i talked to clay and he told me j was seeing someone else already - more confused, i went to the source, it was true and i was left completely confused. 
- EV concert was great... g and el freaked out before adjudication.. but all went well.. i guess... we had 5 pieces. me choreographed one for me and erin that looked nice, brett improved,hip hop etc...
- stagecraft w/meg in the color room...
- light board op for 2 gents. sooo confused and too much time to think that week.
- steve's birthay at rock bottom - i went to dinner, j didnt, i went home, j went to the trappe w/them - still confused, but ready to get over it. 
- started hanging out w/b again. 
- G and Cate for homecomming - b and roger and our banner, walking w/G, football, falling asleep while alumna were on campus.

November: 
-UCDC - jailbirds for life! ruthie's piece. 
- over J, back w/brett practicly - thanksgiving weekend, i was crazy, he loved me, it worked well. we had a great weekend. 
- sig nu dated 
- tried to get a rootbeer keg with j for our party.

December- (choco choco)
- went home w/brett, had fun in the city - cooked for his friends
went to Rep. Dom. had fun in the sun with my family - good pina coladas and margaritas - nice shaded beach, bought a painting, haggled. went to the dance shows... intended on stealing some dance movies, but i never did. video tapped it was fun :)

January - winter training (i wear my sunglasses at night... take me home tonight)
- winter training: 80's party in omwake, felt weird to me, i didnt fit in witht he RAs
- my birthday 17 people out to friday's, 
- spending time w/brett - lost NME elections, began a heavy work load. stressed out.
- Fat kid 2 rush - meg asked me to go to the NME meeting and take marlena's place. i agreed, i became NME. 
- Liz went abroad. Katie came back, we hung out a bit.

one year ago...
may: finished junior year: (nickelback: savin me)
-wrote costa rica paper from thursday to monday morning around graduation. had my first room party with meg, liz, and some of liz's friends - my room was pretty empty but we finished a lot of booze. then we went to the fountains. nicky slept in my room. brett wanted to be friends, some benefits were involved. i started taking physics - brownlowe is an easy teacher, but he's strange.

june: summer
- continued taking physics one and switched to two. the town flooded the day of my final. amie and i took day visits to the beach on saturdays. 

July: summer
- spent the 4th at aunt pat's, started physcis 2. had a cornea transplant on my left eye. malcolm came to visit and i realized that there is such a thing as liking someone only as a friend, and never any more then that. i remember typing physics reports on my dell laptop - sitting on my porch, video taping a bird, etc etc

August: back to school (jojo - too little too late)
didn't finish physics, but tried, i had exam 3, the final and a few papers to do. i moved back early for RA training. we went away to a high ropes course. i met a lot of people, made some new friends. stayed up til 5am talking to Brandon peer, sarah B, Sabir, and a few others, it was a fun night. i climbed a 30ft tall pole with stakes sticking otu of it, to slide down a zip line. 

September: freedom
- went out with ange and trish to maddies, then finished RA training and began the first week of school - ran into jesse for the first time in over a year... and we had that look up and down thing that happens in wismer. tom, steve, me, meg, martha, jay, aj, etc went out for his b-day to rock bottom - then to the movies (tom steven and me) to see beerfest until after 12 when we went to the trappe. meg and i had our bathroom scene "i think him" "really? i don't think so" haha a few hours later.. - next, i stole a mug, then steve drove me back to my house so i could put comfy clothes on, went to drink in jesse's room, played cards - ahmad was there, they took pics and i promply passed out in jesse's bed. after i went to the bathroom... walked out and walked up to him and well... you know... i was a bit forward... but so was he. 
- i thought nothing of that night.. i left early the next day... 2 nights later erin dragged me and liz out to sabir's ... we ended up spooning. and i out drank the soccer team... chugged jack daniels. 
-EV was going well, meg and i were getting close. first kdk party a week later: derek introduced me to his friend, i talked to jesse and teigler hung around me for a while. brett came and i ended up going home with him. nothing happened, just a "wow its been a while" talk. 
I asked jesse to help me with my physics exams... so he pretty much did them for me - we hung out at meg's one night - then he went out and i missed the ride so i hung out with my sisters. 
- CDel's 21st - EV party in Maples - i social hosted along with amy kiyota and jess rhodes. Jesse came over and helped finish my physics - Del called me to ask if i could get liquor and jesse took me to the store, helped me pick it out, carried it, and the mixers and ice - took it all to maples and helped set up - took me to my house, talked to his dad (2nd time while i was there) while i got ready, and took me back. he went home to study... but not for long, he called me and came back - we danced, and then some kid passed out so i had to take care of him. he was gargling so i flipped him and he threw up all over me - the RAs took care of him - i snapped into doctor mode. it was amazing.. until i got a charge of disorderly conduct, and my social hosting privleges taken away. 
- the fringe fest: we performed the season's at UC - i wore catherine's pink dress, and the pics were taken of me and roger dancing. jesse and brett came to watch... and a lot of my other friends, i had stopped talking to derek's friend, and teigler and i were friends.

more soon...

the big news is that i'm single... i have been for the past two weeks. we broke up at the sigma dated... i got upset over something stupid and we fought, and he cracked, flipped out on me and ended it there. i spent the remainder of the night crying my eyes out as my friends dragged me to every party on campus after we got back. I really havnt stoped crying since. 

I was immediately traumatized, its as if a flood of emotions had been dammed up for a long time, and suddently the dam was taken away. i realized everything i did wrong that night and all i wanted was to make things right. I tried his method, i wrote him notes that first week and tried to get him to talk to me - it worked well, we established the bad things... and even joked around a bit. I miss that, his joking around... i miss everything about him - when he's with me that is... i dont miss waiting all night for him to not call and leave me alone. Last saturday my whole ideal of the breakup had been turned upside down when i went to a party and found him and another girl together... that was the most painful thing i've ever seen in my life. and my presence had no affect on him. you all know what happened next. memories of all the fun times we've had together keep running through my mind - i just wish for it to be freshman year again, it was so much fun and i loved him so much... and he loved me. Dance was so hard... i'd sit there and think about him, watch the screen while he was on stage... and just dream and be sappy and all that... i've never been like this before...

When james and i broke up all 3 times... the first time i ran around screaming "i'm free i'm free!!" the second and third i didnt really care... now? i'm a ball of emotions, i dont eat, i dont sleep, i dont get anything done... i just sit and think about him all day - and i just realized how pathetic i am. This is horrible.... why can't we party every weekend like we did last year so i can keep my mind off of this? Why don't any of the boys on this campus like me? why is this girl so much better then me? Yeah... she is though... because i messed up, over and over and i hurt him with my mean ways and he never told me how he felt, never stoped smoking long enough to understand what was going on... fell out of love, and left me. and a week later here she comes... my favorite part is who he compared her to, and i know his opinions of that person... so i guess i should feel releived? im not sure. he used to tell me that i couldn't get over the past... but this one conversation we had... sounds like he's recreating it... it hurts so much to be in the heart broken position. I know how he feels now, it was no surpize that he told me he just wants to be alone... i did too - but neither would let me - and i dont know about this girl and what she's got planned. 

its so hard to accept that after two years of being with someone they can just stop wanting to try, stop wanting to put the time into making it work -and i mean i know i should be glad that i found this out now instead of later but somehow... i dont think this is who he really is...? i mean when we came to school we both drank a lot and had a lot of fun... and yea he has a sketchy side to him... but i dont know... he's so much better then all of that. he used to be so decent. he used to be so caring, and loving... and now he's so cold... i feel like its my fault, i destroyed him. this hurts so bad...

i'd give anything for him to look at me the way he used to... to say goodnight to me one more time... lay with me... curl up the way we used to... call me honey the way he always did when he was happy to see me... flip me upside down on our way to dinner... watch him sleep, sing "you're just too good to be true" to me one more time... let me lay on his stomach to make my headache go away, all the other inapropriate things i can't list that i miss, there's so many things i miss... i just miss him in general... even when things sucked between us, i still miss him. i wish there was something i could do... but he's not in love with me anymore... and he's moving on... leaving me here with my tears, all alone. and it hurts so bad... i keep telling myself i can cry it all out, but the tears never stop. ... he can't see me cry. hell i've seen him cry... i miss that, i miss when he wanted nothing more then to spend an hour talking to me, when we were in the ER and he told me he wanted to marry me, and when i got back together with him that's what i had contemplated out - i had a ring, i was set. too bad i took it off for the show... now i can't wear it again. :(

i went out tonight on an attempt to meet new people and hope to move on... it was ok i guess, bibi dragged me to 302... and i ran into him and it sucked - he was so cold to me, like i didnt even matter. i wonder if i did that to him... i was a horrible person when we were broken up... but i still didnt do half the things he's done in the past 2 weeks. anyways i checked out the guys - bibi says there were 3 after me - one couldn't dance, the second had my zipper pulled down and was working on the button by the time i realized it... thanks ariel for saving me :) and the third got pissed at me b/c i wouldnt hook up (i found him 5 mins later in the corner with another girl). so, clearly i have seen the selection at UC i dont like them, and i hate being single. i feel like a piece of meat, and all these boys want to take a bite.. and nothing more, and brett is turning into one of them with the way he handles girls, drugs, alcohol... emotions, parties... but he's so much better then that!!! UGH!!! why was i so stupid? why did i let him slip away, and spent all my time worrying about all the small stupid shit that doesnt even matter anymore... why??? i want to smack myself, go back in time and fix it. but i cant... and i'm stuck... hopelessly devoted to someone who is completely over me... and it hurts!!

crying myself to sleep, again... hurts

so, since i ran into him for 5 seconds at the party he's come around... kinda odd? it makes sense to me - he's sort of living what i went through last january, but ten fold in speed and intensity. though i have my doubts... i'm not sure exactly what's going on with this boy but i can tell you after the shit he put me through the past two weeks there will be no kiss and makeup, not that easily, i'm not that stupid. no, i have not gotten the chance to fully enjoy being single, and dammit i will before i decide to get back into a relationship. and if i do decide to go back to him someday, that's it, no more "i dont know so let me fuck around for a while whil i figure out" no more dissapearing, no more games, of any kind. 
this boy drives me nuts, i dont understand why he had to do that in front of me... and now wants to talk about things. its like he thinks i'm stupid, and i'll come back whenever he wants me to - yeah i do care about him, love him etc but no, you cannot walk all over me and then expect me to go "ok we can work things out right now" no... after the way he made me feel the past two weeks NO i refuse to give in so easily! or at all for that matter, we'll see. i still feel as though i should give the rest of the male population a chance to show me they're decent - though i know there is no one like brett. I can't go back right after all that pain, think of how horrible i was and i just want to say "ok take me back wee!!" NO!! that fucker hooked up with a girl in front of me, i dont care how honest he was about it, he did it and that's not fair to me at all. now he wants to talk things out and change and shit, what the fuck? ugh still undecided, that was the point... i'm going to bed, making it through the next 2 days and going home away from all of this drama.

The graduation party turned out to be a success - Nick made 2,310$ off of it. The night before i took him and Pat to Steph's house for a BBQ. The whole crew was there, minus Sean and Christine.  We talked about all the good ol' days' memories and ended up burning a hole in the groud.... thats when we found out sprite is flammable - with an attempt to put out the fire by dousing it w/sprite, it shot up into more flames! anyways, so sunday i worked all day, and yesterday was the most boring day in history. Today the family left for JHU for my sister's tri-surgery. She sat on the phone w/me and told me everything that was giong on as if i'd never done it before, it was so cute. :) i heart her. Last night we had a chat and i told her what to expect and how to handle everything... i actually felt like a big sister. Since the family is away, that's the signal for my annual summer gathering and everyone is invited... unless you've punched a wall in my house and left a big bloody mark in my dining room... (Surely not mEntioning Any Names here...) well, time to party-proof the house, do dishes and laundry and then start calling people.... hopefully this wont be as dramatic as last year :)

If the past week didn't take place i'd say my summer has been rather boring. Watching TV got old, I've run out of things to do online, i finished 2 books, and well, you get the point. Last Thursday Brett came to visit. I didn't tell anyone he was comming because i was 99.9% sure he wouldn't show for one reason or another. I guess holding on to that 0.1% of hope is good sometimes :) So we went out to dinner, and went for a walk. Friday he met my kids (I babysit Brady & Rachel) and their parents, and we all played frisbee for a while, then we went to the movies (Star Wars) and Saturday i dragged him around the mall for 5 hours - only b/c i needed a new bathing suite and i'm really picky. I also ended up w/2 pairs of jeans (a rare find! i'm back in a size 00) Sunday i worked and Brett came to visit me. Then we just kinda hung out at home, watched a movie, Monday was pretty much the same, we had a picnic up in Spring Ford by the river - played more frisbee, bbq'd and  made s'mores. Teusday he went home. he left me with a promise to visit in 3 weeks and a message from his mom telling me to visit them soon. 

Wednesday Kelsey and i drove down the Wildwood for the week. We were so excited on the way down - it was a gorgeous day - little did we know that the clouds would come rolling in the second we reached the shore. It stayed cloudy and cold the whole week. Kristen and Lauren, came down later in the day and after a quick trip to the liquar store the drinking began - lotsa card games and Kristen's drunk dialing. We managed to watch quite a few movies - i finally saw the rest of Fight Club along w/Hannibal, Silence of the Lambs, Law&order, "Pregnancy for dummies", The Truth about Cats & Dogs, and...a few others. Thursday the weather was awful and since Kelsey's dad is has connections with this local convent we volunteered to help the nuns set up for a dinner type event. We had to move the chairs.... but they weren't clean, so we cleaned the chairs and then moved them, and some tables. Then the lady working with us thought it would be polite to give us a 2 hour tour of the convent which ended in cookies and soda and carrying electrical supplies to the third floor. (Yippie) it wasn't as bad as it sounds. I found it ironic... most girls come to the beach to pick up a guy, we visited the convent! Caroline and Tamar joined us later in the week. Despite the bad weather, it was a pretty fun trip! 

Lauren and i drove home today and managed to avoid really bad traffic - Tonight i'm taking the time to relax and catch up. Tomorrow i'm taking part in some shady buisness.... not really shady, but someone special can't know what's up until tomorrow @ 2 :) Tootles!

Beach Quotes:

(watching Hannibal) Kristen: I don't know... if I were to date him, he'd have to stop eating people...

(Fear Factor) Guy w/pink shorts: It's all fun and games til' you look like a douche bag on TV!

inner thoughts at the convent :there is no R in "WASH"

there's 2 more... but i have to find them...

It eels like orever since i've updated... a lot has happened ut nothing too dramatic - i've been worn thin the past 2 weeks. the new performing arts center opened last thursday - we rehearsed many times the days before and i got no work done that week. we put on a concert at noon with lindy hop, chris' piece and performance project - and another in the evening with the ballet class and partnering class. kdk's last party of the year was friday night, and i managed to sleep through it. i rushedhome after my chem exam w/ange to see my bro off to prom (he was so handsome and his date is a sweetie). after hanging out for a while ange drove me back to campus and i visited the party in my sweats... went back to change and woke up at 3:30am. apparently brett came to check on me at one point but i dont remember it that well. i needed the sleep though, from the lack of sleep the week before and the weekend before... or was that two weeks ago? not sure anymore, the party before that - airband night! april 8th

airband was so much fun! we danced toa michael jackson medly - won best costume, best theme, best choreography and 3rd place over all. then i social hosted our party and that was pretty interesting - a couple of fights and whatnot. then all i wanted to do was go to sleep but nate and his girl at the time were in bretts room and amie was preoccupied in my room - so we sat in my common room for a while- the boy left and we went to bed in my room. apparently he came back and they decided to initiate some stuff that should not have taken place while there were other people trying to sleep in the room - so after debating on what to do we finally made the scene, got up and left. thank god nate and bibby had fallen asleep already or we would have had no where to sleep that night... for the 4 hours of sleep we got.  

anyways so we went to the collective soul concert the next night and that was ok, not great but not bad. the next weekend was larry's bday party + his girlfriend was in town - brett andi got into a huge fight but no one heard over the loud music. we're hanging in there though... we celebrated our one month, or 16 month whichever anni on the 18th. we decided to have 2 anni's, october 6th (his) and march 18th (mine) which each of us will prepare the evening and such for the other, respectively :)

so the work load is winding down, all my mid semester exams are over but i have a few papers due next week and finals - 4 finals to be exact. the UCDC concert is this week (be there!!) it's great - i'm in two pieces - the first is a lindy hop piece, we're all in random clothing i have an orange dress and there's a lot of us on stage, i dance with Lix (Dave's girl) and Brett - pretty fun! the other piece is amazing - performance project, generated in a class we put together the piece revolving around light - we are all wearing white (dresses/pants) i walk down the stage with my eyes closed to represent birth/innocense/individualism and then victor taps me on the back to spin me arund and then i run at him, to do a gorgeous lift. there's a men's piece, woman's movement chior and two sets of duets - one with 2 women, one with women/men which is mostly choreography from our partnering class. the end, i walk again and everyone runs in criss cross paterns to meet me at the bottom of the stage and a black out. i've seen a few audience members cry over this piece - i'm excited, oh there's also several other lifts (brett gets picked up) and lotsa circle running. nate sings, shane and monica read a poem - we transition from those to music, its a long piece (going on 6 min.) so come see the show!! :) (4/27-4/30 @ 7:30pm in Ritter)

other news... i did my CS house project last weekend, noneof my sister's came but that was expected. i brought 17 people with me, 7 of them were with tau sig and a lot of them were serious runners - it went really well! i'm gonna do it again next year.

so that's all my news, i know ur so glad to hear from me :) i missed the last 2 weeks of gilmore girls, but hopefully trish and i can catch up on that next week! now i'm off to shower and eat before call, and the show :) ciao!

hiya... its gorgeious out today!!! i wanted to spend the whole day outside but i had class from 10-6:30, dinner and then it got dark around 8 - which is awesome!! 
so last week was a hard week - i had a bio exam wednesday (91%) dance showing wednesday night (went really well), chem exam friday, and friday was april fools day - the anniversary of Steve Ayeres' death = bad day for the class of 2003. Friday night we ended up hanging out with Meghan and Scott (yep my stage manager) so of course ACTF drama got brought up and Brett voiced his opinion of it all very loudly and we fought the whole way home until i sat there and firmly stated over and over that he has nothing to worry about, so now he knows, he's learning more and more every day. I've begun wearing the ring on my left finger - partially because my mom insists that's where its supposed to go and partially because the weather change has made my joints swell up. (i'm right-handed) so that works for him.
i slept all day saturday, litterally - i woke up, went to lunch, slept, ate food, showered and went to see Sin City - good movie! a little confusing but i think i can clear that up by watching it again. They turned my Rory (Alexis Bledel) into a hooker! she did good though, a betraying hooker at that! she did wear the most clothes out of all of them though, which saved her innocent reputation a lil bit lol.
Sunday i worked... Mark Exley is keeping our pay checks until we talk to him about what trainings we owe... so i left a really mean voice mail for him and when andrew called me back (because mark is a little b... and can't reap what he sews, so he has andrew do the dirty work) so andrew appologized and told me i wasnt missing anything (doh) and said he'd mail my check out. drama over nothing, seriously! i'm glad its solved though, i'm just gonna bring ear plugs to the staff meeting this Sunday. 
Room lottery was the other night - so i'll be living in 305 next year which is a single - not the single i wanted but i can deal i guess... it has slanted cealings, very slanted! and only one window which sucks because i love windows. I'm kinda scared of living alone, i'm so used to having someone else in the room with me when i go to sleep - i hate sleeping in a room alone. i hate the bathroom up there too, no windows. I'll deal though i guess. i'll prolly end up moving into reimert, or have brett move in w/me if he gets sick of nate and bibby... bippy... how do u spell that?? Bogdona is her real name, she's nates new girlfriend. Dave also has a love interest named Liz who is my Lindy Hop partner. She's a sweety, she went to the movies w/us saturday. OH and after the movies we broke into the PAC to see the new theaters - ITS HUGE!!! like the one i performed on at ACTF, amazing! but no where near done! the blackbox, thats slightly larger then ours is almost done so we'll have that. but all in all i was amazed! I can't wait to perform there in the fall!
So that's all, my mom's Aunt Ronnie (Veronica) died today - she's been battling cancer since i was little and it was sad to see her go even though my side of the family didnt get along with her (not going into details, big family argument over the past 6 months) 

so that's about all that's new with me, i'll post a more emotional entry sometime later this week - since the week is so light i havnt been motivated to do any work lol so i'm sure i'll get to it, <3 keep commenting! shows me u love me!

Soooo today... i was approved to do research in the fall w/Dr. Bailey!!! not as exciting for everyone, but its a big thing cos she's the first prof. i really asked :) so i'm going to be working with cardiac function and dysfunction and rabbitts, sad i know but it'll be good experience for my dream job. 
Last week i got rediculously sick, fallowed by saturday night when i got rediculously drunk. Thursday i was in bed all night with a fever,tummy ache, pale skin, high eye & sinus & head pressure, migrane symptoms yadda yadda joint pain, dizziness, everything under the sun except excretion. (yuck) so i went to the dr. friday and the lab work today shows that i have strep throat - amoxicilin will kill it off! Today's one of those days that make me want to sleep until the next chapter of my life begins. Once again interupting my homework to present a new thought... actually Dashboard took me back once again to last year. I'm realizing how differant i was from who i am now... and i dont like either person, I wish i could be a mix of both... example

Type A: I was free, in the moment, emotional about everything. it seemed to me that i was more social, and i enjoyed meeting new people. I did care about homework but somehow i complained about it so much that it was never finished. however... looking back on some of my more private entries i wrote with ease, emotion, much more emotion then i can put in now. I not only listened to music, but i really heard it. however, i was always stressed out and i felt as though i were flying from place to place and not endulging in the moment, i miss the freshman feel that i had last year and never took pleasure in. I was too busy fleeing from the stressful vibes that my roomate gave off, or just managing to finish that paper half-ass before midnight. I never really partied, in fact i think i'm more comfortable at parties now then i was in type A. I flew everywhere... never had a moment to relax, but i was crazy, i always had something on my mind and not enough time to do it.

Type B sophomore year, i know the ropes. Nothing is changing, stability - the thing for which i strived most last year. I longed for stability, in fact i thought i was a stable loving person. How boring i must have wished to be. I have time for everything now, i plan everything. Nothing is changing, I feel comfortable where i am even though i still miss the stillness of home and the woods and my crew from the ville. I was told to take things easy this year... so i have been - and i've been doing a pretty good job with it, but i miss being free.

     I dont know exactly how to describe free because there is no physical cercumstance that makes me free or not free. I'm not entirely sure who i want to be... I need to be busy, but isnt that just a product of society? the need to be doing something at all times. I'm not sure... Who am I anyway? Am I shooting too far out of my league? or will i do something great one day by seeming crazy now? Do opposites really attract or is it a temporary arraingment that will soon falter and fade? For a while i stopped wanting to fly, i thought stepping up the ladder was the right way to go... fly or climb? Thi is so random...

"well this is incredible, starving, unsatiable, yes this is love for the first time - we'd like to think that we were all invincible yeah well didnt we all once... before we felt lost for the first time"

wasnt i lost last year? lost can be fun, it teaches you who your real friends are... they're the ones who find you. what do i want? i dont want material things, i want to fly, i want to be around people who inspire me to want to fly... perhaps someday i will fly away... but i love home... i would come back after a time... am i an artist or do i fallow the scientific method... i'm so lost... perhaps i'm only pretending to be found... i'm sorry for the confusion and randomness.

I'm just going to come out and say it this year... i'm scared of going back to school. I can't wait to see all my friends and get back in a routine, but i miss home too. I know, i live 10 minutes away from home but its so differant. I'm afraid of what my classes will bring... hard work, mean teachers, more medical disbeleif, i realized last year how small of a person i am and how little time people are willing to take with me. Most of all, going back to school means another chapter in my life is closed and that we're all growing up... too fast. I wish i could have frozen life last summer. I'll never forget, Steph, Sean and i were out camping - i woke up early as always and i thought that i could die right there and be happy with my life... except my love life which had been traumatic before college. But love wasn't important, friendship was and that i truly had for the first time, or so i thought. The one thing i wished for going into college is that i would have friends to help me along the way - i successfully have friends, and i'm happy. I never once felt lonely living on campus, the only problem was that i felt unsure of myself - who i am, who i want to be, the entire year. I've never had to explain my medical situation to people before without mom there to back me up, the deans office called her and told her that they didnt beleive me - that upset me more then anything. Why wouldnt they beleive me? cant you look itno my eyes and see the stitches, the whiter then white scars from the past? i didnt understand, I think i'm just being oversensative about it, and now that i've been exposed to more adult criticism i'll handle it better. It is kinda odd that my peers accept me but the adults don't... i'm used to things the other way around lol. Oh well, looking back on things i really am glad i went to UC last year, and i'm partially looking forward to going back. I dont think i'll ever be ready to endulge in wismer food for another semester, but freedom from needing a ride everywhere sounds so nice :)  I'm posting some stuff i wrote in Ohio, when Brett came back from the dead - check it out, it should be in the June 20-25 era lol good luck

This computer, only like 9 months old, has too many viruses on it from my brother... so i cant type in color. this irritates me because i like to take care of things, not destroy them. whatever, i have my own computer. 

so surgery was all i thought it was going to be, painful. seeing other surgeries was fun... but next time i think i'm going to go against my parents and suggest that i am not on the OR list the day i observe. I couldnt eat from 12am to 5:30pm the next day... and it got to me a lil bit. so the first case was a little boy who had what they call "u.v.itis" which is short for something... but i dont know the full name. he had 4 surgeries performed in one day, poor kid. His cornea was scrapped (to remove calcium deposits caused by the disease) then he had part of his iris carved out (to increase liquad flow) then he had a cataract extraction, and finaly a tube shunt put in. When i saw him at post-op this morning he seemed less then thrilled. 

the next case was an older lady. she had a cataract extraction as well as a shunt implant. i didnt get to see the whole surgery because i had to register for my surgery... blah

so for me, i couldnt get away without an IV - but this was my first surgery without general anesthesia. so i was wide awake with some numbing eye drops and 2 injections of pain killers. he put in like 10 stitches to cover the leak, and then stitched up the bottom of my eye so that the shunt wouldnt stick out as much (ever see the white bubbley stuff at the bottom of my eye? it should be gone now) he also removed the stitch that surrounded the tube that he implanted in May. so my pressure is a bit low, but things look good so far. 

Tensions: L=7  R=19

I go back in 2 weeks, and i will visit the OR as an observer over winter break. Being awake was strange... they cover EVERYTHING but the eye they're working in. they clamp that eye open - it quickly dries out and your vision is blurred the whole time... the lights are bright, and the last 3 stitches were painful. I had a good grasp on the cords that were laying on my right side because of the pain lol but it all went away, now i just have that normal burning sensation from the stitches. before my surgery, i got to spend some time in the staff room - it was so funny a couple people looked at me like "what the f... i know her... dont i??" it was fun meeting all the nurses who've taken care of me over the years. they all picked on me because i couldnt eat - and i got to meet my regular doctor's grandson, he's such a cutie! 

so that's all for now... i've been trying to sleep but that's proving impossible around this house so i'm gonna do some light packing, phone calls are more then welcome!

9 week post-op appointment.

Tensions: L = 20   R = 11

My right eye finally stabalized at a low pressure. The left eye is doing well too, however the leak has not healed after 2 weeks with a bandage contact. The call is to have my 38th operation to insert a few stitches and remove a stitch from the 37th operation site. This should be happening August 6th - the same day that i will be observing surgeries in the OR. I will just take the place of the last case - since it will be done with topical anesthesia i wont have to go through most of the pre-op procedures. Topical (spelt as it sounds) means that my eye will be numbed through an injection straight to the site of surgery. I will be fully awake and able to move my eye, just not feel the sewing - i hope anyway :) No IV necesarry (YaY!!) Unfortunetly i still have to stay over night for a post-op the next day, which sucks because i wanted Brett to visit that weekend, oh well. I'm exhausted and my eye is irritated so i think i'm going to stay in tonight, going out tomorrow night sounds fun though, any takers? :) g'night!

Today I got to play med. student for a day -- it was fun! Dr. Congdon treated me like one of his colleagues. I got to observe patients eye's through a learning scope (a microscope attached to the main slit-lamp, so 2 people can see the same thing) Its amazing how many parts of the eye there are - i mean i had seen all the diagrams and learned about everything but to actually see it was amazing. Everyone's iris is so differant - and i got to see a fair ammount of differant disorders. I saw the effects of basically every surgery that i've had completed. It takes a lot of patience to keep a clinic running - jumping from one patient to another without a break between - keeping all their medical history in the back of your mind and diagnosing & making future plans - it does sound like a lot - but i'm sure when you get to know your patients it gets easier. I also noticed that my doctor takes extra care with my eyes, verses the other patients he saw today. This is the same type of care i've always received, maybe he does see some potential in me. He always explained things a lot more to me then he does to his other patients. Interesting, anyways. Apparently i'm too small for a regular white jacket, so being dressed up had to do.
One patient was having a stitch removed - apparently he had a problem keeping his eye still (his own fault) and ended up with a scratch across his cornea - those arent fun, but he should have held still... or at least not darted his eyes all the way to the other side of his head.
I want to see my own eyes, as weird as that sounds - i'm sure its not impossible - they can set up a monitor or film it or something, maybe i'll ask them to do it someday. My next adventure is to play med. student in the O.R. sometime in August  - i'm very excited about that, and i hope i dont get creeped out, i dont think i will. I'll have to stop by the recovery room, all the nurses know me well there lol. It'd be nice to see their faces for once, and say hi without bandages and an IV attached. and that's all for now - back to being a kid!

Post op: 48 days

Pressure: L : 3 R: 22

Right eye is a little high but nothing to worry about yet. the left eye however, pressure dropped over night after being at a reasonable level for the past week. My doctor diagnosed that when I started exercising yesterday I worked myself too hard - and tore my eye open. There is a small tear in the far left corner of my eye. Treatment is a huge contact lens that I am to wear for the next week - I'm taking cosopt twice a day now in effort to slow down the flow of liquad in my eye to give the tear time to heal. Pred forte is down to twice a day... not sure why. Anywho the doc went ahead and told me not to do any type of activity until the tear heals - so no running, lifting, bending, basically anything especially stressing out. Next week I get to play JHU med student for a day!! :)

it all came pouring back up... 2 great hurls and out it came! all the barium i drank this morning. the techs & dr.s felt so awful. I was shaking from the trauma - my eyes hurt, and i broke into a sweat. My stomach is still uneasy - i've eaten bread and tea but the acid burn has not stopped. I hope they figured out what's wrong with me because i'm going to be very pessimistic about doing that again.

We paniced and rushed to JHU to see the glaucoma specialists who said it was just a scratch and then put me through a million tests to find out why my pressure went down.

So i had the local Dr. take my pressures yesterday because i've become addicted to knowing what they are at all times and 3 weeks was too long to go without a reading.

Pressure: L=16 R=17

Very nice, a lil on the high side but i expected them to float down to the lower teens - however later in the day i spent a lot of time on the computer and then went for a long walk. durring my walk i noticed i couldnt see very well so i closed the left eye but it wasnt until i was watching satc that i realized my pressure had nose dived to like 5 or so... it feels like i just had surgery my eye is soft and i can't see straight, i see lil swirlies of bright color and its weeping lots of tears and mucus. Neither of my Doctors are in the office today so there is no chance of me figuring outwhat happend until tomorrow - so i pumped myself up with tylenal3codine so that the low-pressure pain would stop (every time my muscles move, it pushes the eye and at a low pressure its painful) so that's my interesting day... :( I'm scared to find out what happened.
